The council has apologised to residents for the inconvenience as the heavy rains were beyond its control. JOHANNESBURG The City of Tshwane says it has now managed to restore power to most areas which experienced outages following a massive storm over the weekend. Most areas in the metro including the north, east and west of Pretoria, were left with no electricity, had blocked sewers and fallen trees. The Citys apologised to residents for the inconvenience as the heavy rains were beyond its control. Tshwane spokesperson Selby Bokaba says their teams are on site attending to damage and restoring the remaining services which have been affected. We started by prioritising the area outage, and we think now we are done with the area outage. We are now focusing on individual complaints.